org.jcvi.jillion.internal.core

Class EncodedSequence<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.internal.core.EncodedSequence<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Sequence<T>

    public abstract class EncodedSequence<T>
extends Object
implements Sequence<T>
    EncodedSequence is a composite object containing a byte representation of data and an GlyphCodec to decode it. This allows Sequence data to be encoded in different forms to take up the minimal amount of memory possible for a given situation.
    Author:
    dkatzel
